Group Description: The Valuations Group performs all financial analysis for Invesco Real Estate’s US direct real estate portfolio, valued at over $31 billion. The group performs the processes for establishing fair market values for the underlying assets through third party appraisals and internal valuations. These valuations are required for financial reporting, client reporting, and performance benchmarking. The primary property types include office, retail, industrial, and multi-family. The independent group is tasked with the execution of a process designed to value assets with as much objectivity as possible. An important part of the function is to balance the competing perspectives of investment professionals involved in the internal processes to ensure that supportable data is the primary consideration in deriving unbiased valuations. This work is necessary for all of the Advisor’s product lines including open end funds, closed end value add funds, closed end strategic opportunistic funds, an open-end debt fund, and separate account clients. Understanding the structure and investment premises of these funds and their underlying assets will be critical to providing quality work. Key Responsibilities: Perform financial modeling such as discounted cash flow for unleveraged structures. Coordinate with all levels of management to gather and analyze data, summarize findings, and prepare recommendations regarding conclusions. Facilitate the third-party appraisal process as directed by client requirements, including reviewing and auditing the appraisals and writing review comments with market support for findings. Present valuation analyses and assumptions to senior members of asset management and portfolio management. Other duties as assigned.
